puzzle.help: 1. Divide the field in enclosures, so that sheep are separated from wolves. 2. Each enclosure must contain either sheep or wolves (but not both) and must not be empty. 3. The lines (fencing) of the enclosures start and end on the edges of the grid. 4. Lines only turn at posts (dots). 5. Lines can cross each other except posts (dots). 6. Not all posts must be used.
